Add HTTP code 413 as permanent error

Code 413 is defined as "Payload Too Large" (The request is larger than the server is willing or able to process).
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes#4xx_Client_Error

This might be needed when the backend responds that it's either entirely out of space or the request exceeds the quota.
Neither of the previous permanent errors (415, 500, 501) corresponded to this situation.

Delayed retries appear as pending with progress > 0

By @tpodom to resolve #61.

When using the delayed retry interval a chunk will be reset with the
xhr as null.
As a result, the chunk appears as pending and is available to be sent
once another
finishes.  However, if it gets sent and then the timer fires the same
chunk will be
sent a second time (possibly simultaneously).

Since the loaded value isn't cleared on abort the progress for a chunk
pending
retry also reports its progress as how far the chunk got before the
failure.  This
can result in a chunk being 100% sent but failed on the server and the
fileSuccess
firing before the chunk is actually completed.
Added a version number to resolve #85.
Solves #91 and solves #80

Merge pull request #10 from EnTeQuAk/fix_chromium_performance

Cache the original file size.

Cache the original file size.

This works around a performance problem using Chromium 19+ (in my tests).
Huge amounts of calls to $.fileObj.file.size for example to render a
progress bar lead to huge performance decrease compared to other browsers like
Firefox.
Firefox 13 has gone back to using .slice() instead of the prefixed .mozSlice()
Firefox 12 is set to change the behaviour for . Have removed any timeout for when the server must respond.

Slight change in the chunking of files in order for the last chunk actually to contain data (this is useful for video files where meta data might be present the last chunk). The last chunk might be >chunkSize, but will be <2*chunkSize.
